      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "function makeJsonCompatible(text) { \n  return JSON.stringify(text); \n}\n\nfunction makePrompt(text) {\n  return `\nYou are an email analysis assistant.\n\nFrom the email below:\n\n1) Write a concise but complete summary including key details (deadlines, requests, payments, meetings, links, decisions).\n2) Extract any explicit deadline (or None).\n3) Extract all important URLs (or None).\n4) Additional remarks (if any).\n\nEmail Body:\n${text}\n\nReturn information exactly as this list:\n1. **summary** ,\n2. **extracted_deadline**: \"string or None\",\n3. **extracted_links** \n4. **Additional Notes**\n`;\n}\n\nconst rawText = $input.first().json.content;\nconst subject = $input.first().json.subject;\nconst sender_name = $input.first().json.senderName;\nconst sender_email = $input.first().json.senderEmail;\nconst date = $input.first().json.date;\n\n// No JSON.stringify here\nconst prompt = makePrompt(rawText);\nconst safeText = makeJsonCompatible(rawText);\nconst safePrompt = makeJsonCompatible(prompt);\nconst safeSubject = makeJsonCompatible(subject);\nconst safeSenderName = makeJsonCompatible(sender_name);\nconst safeSenderEmail = makeJsonCompatible(sender_email);\nconst safeDate = makeJsonCompatible(date);\nreturn [\n  {\n    json: {\n      prompt: safePrompt,\n      subject: safeSubject,\n      senderEmail: safeSenderEmail,\n      senderName: safeSenderName,\n      date: safeDate,\n      text: safeText,\n    }\n  }\n];"
      },
